cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image restoration problems. The use of generative models with adversarial learning suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of physics models and constraints suggests that it could also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the use of extensive experiments suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
